Springboks lock Eben Etzebeth is reportedly taking the South African Human Rights Commission to court. JOHANNESBURG - Springbok lock Eben Etzebeth is taking legal action against the Human Rights Commission. Etzebeth wants the decision to move the case to the equality court on review. The so-called Langebaan four are accusing Etzebeth of hurling racial slurs at them. READ: SAHRC: We are not prejudiced against Etzebeth They want over R1-million in compensation and an apology. The commission's Buang Jones' comments on making an example of Etzebeth, drew harsh criticism.